{{Quote|There is nothing I may say. You know our ways, Tholme. We can disclose nothing about a contract.|[[Akku Seii]] to Tholme|<ref name="Star Wars: Republic: Trackdown">''[[Star Wars: Republic: Trackdown]]''</ref>}}
The '''Anzati Code of Honor''' forbid telling the contracts or the [[Death/Legends|kills]]. Many [[Anzat (species)|Anzati]] were [[Assassin/Legends|assassins]], and were hired to murder anyone. So, the Code of Honor was created to hide this secret information to the public face when they committed a crime. When [[Tholme/Legends|Tholme]] asked the Anzati Assassin master [[Akku Seii]] about the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Sora Bulq/Legends|Sora Bulq]], the Code protected the information. It also happened when [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]] asked [[Sajé Tasha]], who was hired to kill the former [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Finis Valorum/Legends|Finis Valorum]].

